{"_id":"BkJY05W9W","title":"Lesson 4: (4) Methods","body":{"entityMap":{},"blocks":[{"key":"ag6qs","text":"Lesson 4: (4) Methods","type":"header-one","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5otmn","text":"Three built in methods for workign with collections - each, select, map","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":54,"length":17,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d6mij","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"blr3o","text":"each  --> Returns the original collection","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":41,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bikqj","text":"A method to loop over a Ruby collection in a much more succinct manner.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"46pjn","text":"Example usage:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"813g6","text":"[1,2,3].each do |num|","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5hd8","text":"  put num","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1j6c1","text":"end","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"99mq3","text":"#outputs","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7nfbs","text":"#1","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6809q","text":"#2","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6c52n","text":"#3","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4sqal","text":"#|num| is the argument for the block which takes the current iteration value.","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dl7pc","text":"","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4oal6","text":"hash = {a:1, b:2, c:3}","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5jrat","text":"hash.each do |key, value|","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eu4ou","text":"  puts \"The key is #{key} and the value is #{value}\"","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3pbi2","text":"end","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6pujg","text":"#outputs","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2t3oi","text":"#The key is a and the value is 1","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8v26d","text":"#The key is b and the value is 2","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2cqkc","text":"#The key is c and the value is 3","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"13hoj","text":"select","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":6,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d5df4","text":"To perform selection, select evaluates the return value of the block. The block returns a value on each iteration, which then gets evaluated by select. Similar to a real method, the return value of the block is the return value of the last expression of the block.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":22,"length":7,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7oaur","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctf27","text":"When an element is selected it is placed in a new collection. It will return a new collection containing all the selected elements.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"au8se","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f55uf","text":"map","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":0,"length":3,"style":"BOLD"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"795sl","text":"Map also considers the return value of the block. map uses the return value of the block to perform a transformation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1luv2","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e9qmm","text":" [1, 2, 3].map do |num|\n  num * 2\nend","type":"custom-code-block-ruby","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8bjau","text":"The return value of the block is the product of num and 2. map then takes this value and places it in a new collection.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"j3r","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"clnrf","text":"Reference Table","type":"header-two","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c13nh","text":"\n","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bjrhe","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dgauc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cam9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"59kd9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}]},"dateCreated":"2017-09-09T17:01:42.736Z","lastUpdated":"2017-09-09T17:27:30.306Z"}
